(10, '', 'Shaun Wong', 'Late Trip Notice - Castle Hil, Saturday, 11Nov 2017 at 8.00am\nCastle Hill Peak is a CTC classic, and the spring conditions mean this could be an chance to get to (nearly) 2000m without snow gear, or maybe we will be lucky and have some fresh spring snow to play in, who knows. The walk will be the standard\" approach from Porters pass (yes we will cheat and drive half of our altitude gain!) and approach via foggy peak at a slow pace. If time, conditions and inclination allow we might wonder on towards The Gap, but we will definitely return the way we came. Meet at Papanui Z Station at 8am. \n\nTo join this trip please contact Lorraine Poole at 03 332 2864 candl.poole@gmail.com\n', 0, '', '2017-11-07 08:25:06'),
